1. User writes note in text field
2. User clicks Save button
3. Browser sends POST request to /exampleapp/new_note with note data
4. Server receives POST, saves note to database
5. Server responds with 302 redirect to /exampleapp/notes
6. Browser receives redirect, sends GET request to /exampleapp/notes
7. Server sends back the HTML page
8. Browser renders page, which triggers more requests:
   - GET /main.css (gets styles)
   - GET /main.js (gets JavaScript)
   - GET /data.json (gets note data)
9. Browser displays updated notes list
